essential_items.description: Core items that should appear in most stores

notes.design_philosophy: Zava DIY operates a network of regional hardware stores across the USA, each with curated product selection based on local climate and customer needs
agent_use_cases: Customer asks for product not in current store - agent finds it at another location or online
Store needs to reorder popular items - agent checks inventory at other stores
Customer wants to know which store has specific product in stock
Agent suggests alternative stores based on product availability and location
notes.store_id_format: Uses human-readable alphanumeric IDs: NYC001=New York, SF001=San Francisco, AUS001=Austin, etc.
notes.data_structure: Consolidated store reference with location data, business metrics, product assignments, and seasonal configurations
notes.product_overlap: Each physical store carries 150-200 SKUs selected for regional relevance and customer demand
notes.online_store: Zava DIY Online Store carries all products with nationwide shipping
